This project demonstrates how four LEDs are independently controlled using four relays interfaced with an ESP32 microcontroller ğŸ§ âš¡. The entire system is designed and tested using the Wokwi online simulator, making it easy to learn and debug without physical hardware.

Each relay acts as an electrically isolated switch ğŸ”„ that safely controls one LED. The ESP32 sends digital ON/OFF signals to the relay module, allowing each LED to be switched independently. This project helps in understanding relay interfacing, digital output control, and multi-channel switching systems.

The logic is written in Arduino IDE for ESP32, where different GPIO pins are assigned to the relays. By changing the output states in the code, the LEDs can be turned ON or OFF accordingly âœ…âŒ.

